(60, 1, 1, 44, 2, 5, 11, NULL, 'Connection of Scattered Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the geographical regions of Pontus and Cappadocia, highlighting the dispersion of believers. This connection illustrates the spread of the Gospel to diverse audiences, as seen in the gathering of Jews from various nations.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 1, 59, 1, 1, 1, 'scattered', 'Scattered Believers Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of believers who are ''scattered.'' Peter addresses ''strangers scattered throughout'' various regions, while James writes to ''the twelve tribes which are scattered abroad.'' This connection highlights the shared experience of dispersion among early Christians.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 1, 58, 11, 13, 13, 'strangers', 'Strangers and Pilgrims Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''strangers'' on earth. In 1 Peter, Peter addresses ''strangers scattered'' in various regions, while Hebrews speaks of those who ''confessed that they were strangers and pilgrims.'' This connection highlights a shared theme of faith and identity among believers.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 1, 49, 2, 19, 19, 'strangers', 'Strangers and Fellow Citizens', 'This connection highlights the transition from being ''strangers'' to becoming part of the ''household of God.'' Both passages emphasize the communal aspect of faith and belonging.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 1, 44, 8, 4, 4, 'scattered', 'Scattering and Preaching Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of believers being ''scattered'' and their subsequent actions. Both passages emphasize the movement of Christians to various regions and their commitment to spreading the word.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 1, 60, 2, 11, 11, 'strangers', 'Strangers and Pilgrims Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of believers as ''strangers.'' This connection highlights the theme of living in a world that is not one''s own, encouraging a lifestyle of abstaining from worldly desires.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 1, 19, 44, 11, 11, 'scattered', 'Scattering Among Nations', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of scattering among different groups. In 1 Peter, the believers are described as ''strangers scattered,'' while Psalms speaks of being ''scattered among the heathen.'' This connection highlights the experience of displacement and alienation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 2, 53, 2, 13, 13, 'sanctification of the Spirit', 'Connection of Election and Sanctification', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of election and sanctification by the Spirit. They highlight the role of God''s foreknowledge and the process leading to salvation.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 2, 49, 1, 4, 5, 'Elect according to the foreknowledge of God', 'Election and Predestination Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being chosen by God before the foundation of the world. They highlight the role of the Spirit and Jesus Christ in the process of sanctification and adoption.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 2, 58, 12, 24, 24, 'sprinkling of the blood of Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Blood Sprinkling', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''blood of sprinkling,'' linking the sanctification process in 1 Peter with the new covenant in Hebrews. This connection highlights the significance of Jesus'' blood in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 2, 60, 1, 22, 22, 'obedience', 'Connection of Purification and Obedience', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of obedience and purification through the Spirit. The first verse mentions ''obedience'' and ''sanctification of the Spirit,'' while the second focuses on ''purified your souls in obeying the truth.''', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 2, 45, 11, 2, 2, 'foreknowledge of God', 'Foreknowledge of God', 'Both passages emphasize God''s foreknowledge in relation to His people. In 1 Peter, it highlights the elect according to God''s foreknowledge, while Romans reaffirms that God has not cast away those He foreknew.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 2, 43, 15, 16, 19, 'Elect according to the foreknowledge', 'Chosen and Elect', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine selection, as both passages emphasize that believers are chosen by God. In 1 Peter, the elect are described as chosen according to God''s foreknowledge, while in John, Jesus states, ''Ye have not chosen me, but I have chosen you.''', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 2, 44, 2, 23, 23, 'foreknowledge of God', 'Connection of Foreknowledge of God', 'Both passages emphasize the ''foreknowledge of God,'' linking God''s divine plan in the salvation of believers and the crucifixion of Jesus. This connection highlights the intentionality behind God''s actions in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 3, 60, 1, 23, 23, 'begotten us again unto a lively hope', 'Connection of New Birth', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''born again'' through God''s action. The first passage highlights being begotten to a ''lively hope'' by the resurrection, while the second specifies being born of ''incorruptible seed'' by the word of God.', 'theme', 0.6499999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 3, 62, 5, 4, 4, 'begotten us again unto a lively hope', 'Hope and Overcoming the World', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''born of God'' in both passages. In 1 Peter, believers are ''begotten... unto a lively hope,'' while 1 John states that those ''born of God'' overcome the world through faith.', 'theme', 0.608, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 3, 45, 15, 13, 13, 'hope', 'Connection of Hope in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of hope, with 1 Peter highlighting a ''lively hope'' through the resurrection and Romans expressing the desire to ''abound in hope'' through the Holy Spirit. This connection highlights the continuity of hope as a central theme in the Christian faith.', 'theme', 0.58, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 3, 56, 3, 4, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Mercy and Hope', 'Both passages emphasize God''s mercy in salvation. 1 Peter highlights being ''begotten... unto a lively hope,'' while Titus speaks of being saved ''according to his mercy.'' This connection highlights the transformative power of God''s mercy through Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 3, 49, 1, 7, 7, 'lively hope', 'Connection of Redemption and Hope', 'Both passages emphasize the themes of redemption and hope through Jesus Christ. 1 Peter highlights being ''begotten... unto a lively hope'' by the resurrection, while Ephesians speaks of ''redemption through his blood'' as a source of forgiveness.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 3, 47, 1, 3, 3, 'abundant mercy', 'Connection of Blessings and Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of blessing God, highlighting His mercy. The source verse mentions ''abundant mercy,'' while the target verse refers to ''the Father of mercies.''', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 3, 45, 12, 12, 12, 'lively hope', 'Connection of Hope and Prayer', 'This connection highlights the theme of hope found in both passages. 1 Peter 1:3 speaks of a ''lively hope'' through the resurrection, while Romans 12:12 encourages believers to ''rejoice in hope,'' linking the concepts of hope and perseverance in faith.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 4, 66, 21, 27, 27, 'undefiled', 'Inheritance and Purity', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of purity and incorruptibility in relation to the inheritance reserved for believers. The ''undefiled'' inheritance in 1 Peter connects with the idea that nothing defiled can enter the new creation in Revelation.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 4, 58, 9, 15, 15, 'inheritance incorruptible', 'Connection of Eternal Inheritance', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of an ''inheritance'' that is eternal and reserved for believers. 1 Peter speaks of an ''inheritance incorruptible'' while Hebrews refers to a ''promise of eternal inheritance,'' highlighting the continuity of this theme.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 4, 60, 5, 4, 4, 'that fadeth not away', 'Inheritance and Glory Connection', 'Both passages emphasize rewards that do not fade away. The incorruptible inheritance in 1 Peter 1:4 parallels the crown of glory in 1 Peter 5:4, highlighting the enduring nature of these blessings.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 4, 55, 4, 8, 8, 'reserved in heaven for you', 'Inheritance and Reward Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a reward reserved in heaven for believers. 1 Peter speaks of an inheritance that is incorruptible, while 2 Timothy refers to a crown of righteousness laid up for those who love the Lord''s appearing.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 4, 51, 1, 5, 5, 'reserved in heaven for you', 'Heavenly Inheritance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of hope and inheritance reserved in heaven. They highlight the assurance of a future reward that is incorruptible and eternal.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 4, 40, 25, 34, 34, 'inheritance incorruptible, and undefiled', 'Inheritance and Kingdom Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of inheritance, with 1 Peter referring to an incorruptible inheritance reserved in heaven, while Matthew speaks of inheriting a kingdom prepared from the foundation of the world. This connection highlights the promise of eternal rewards for believers.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 4, 23, 40, 7, 8, 'fadeth not away', 'Connection of Inheritance and Permanence', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between temporary things and what endures. 1 Peter speaks of an inheritance that ''fadeth not away,'' while Isaiah highlights that ''the grass withereth, the flower fadeth.'' This connection highlights the permanence of God''s promises compared to the transience of earthly life.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 5, 50, 1, 6, 6, 'power of God through faith', 'God''s Assurance in Salvation', 'This connection highlights the assurance of God''s ongoing work in believers. Both passages emphasize God''s power and faithfulness in bringing salvation to completion.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 5, 49, 2, 8, 8, 'through faith', 'Connection of Salvation Through Faith', 'Both passages emphasize salvation through faith, highlighting that it is not of ourselves but a divine gift. This connection underscores the role of God''s power and grace in the process of salvation.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 5, 45, 8, 31, 39, 'kept by the power of God', 'Connection of Divine Protection', 'Both passages emphasize the power of God in safeguarding believers. 1 Peter 1:5 speaks of being kept by God''s power, while Romans 8:31-39 assures that if God is for us, no one can stand against us.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 5, 53, 2, 13, 14, 'faith unto salvation', 'Connection of Salvation and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation and the role of faith. 1 Peter highlights being kept by God''s power through faith, while 2 Thessalonians speaks of being chosen for salvation through belief in the truth.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 5, 18, 19, 25, 25, 'salvation ready to be revealed', 'Connection of Redemption and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of salvation and the assurance of a redeemer. Job expresses confidence in a future redeemer, while 1 Peter speaks of salvation ready to be revealed, linking the hope of redemption across time.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 5, 43, 10, 28, 30, 'kept by the power of God', 'Salvation and Divine Protection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being kept by God''s power in both passages. 1 Peter emphasizes being kept through faith for salvation, while John assures believers of eternal life and protection from being lost.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 5, 60, 1, 13, 13, 'salvation ready to be revealed', 'Connection of Hope and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hope in salvation. The first verse speaks of being kept for salvation, while the second encourages hope for grace at the revelation of Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 6, 59, 1, 2, 2, 'temptations', 'Joy in Trials Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejoicing amidst trials. Both passages emphasize the experience of ''temptations'' and encourage a joyful response despite difficulties.', 'theme', 0.601, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 6, 60, 5, 10, 10, NULL, 'Suffering and Restoration Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the experience of suffering as a temporary state. They highlight the eventual restoration and strengthening that follows this period of heaviness and trials.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 6, 45, 12, 12, 12, 'greatly rejoice', 'Rejoicing in Trials', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of rejoicing despite difficulties. 1 Peter speaks of rejoicing amid temptations, while Romans encourages rejoicing in hope during tribulation.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 6, 45, 5, 2, 2, 'ye greatly rejoice', 'Rejoicing in Trials and Hope', 'Both passages emphasize rejoicing despite challenges. 1 Peter speaks of rejoicing amid ''manifold temptations,'' while Romans highlights rejoicing in ''hope of the glory of God.'' This connection highlights the theme of finding joy in faith during difficult times.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 6, 40, 5, 12, 12, 'greatly rejoice', 'Rejoicing Amidst Trials', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of rejoicing despite suffering. In 1 Peter, believers are encouraged to rejoice during trials, while Matthew highlights rejoicing in the face of persecution, linking both to the promise of future reward.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 6, 23, 61, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Joy and Mourning', 'Both passages emphasize the transition from heaviness to joy. 1 Peter speaks of rejoicing despite temptations, while Isaiah promises joy and beauty in exchange for mourning and heaviness.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 6, 43, 16, 33, 33, 'manifold temptations', 'Connection of Tribulation and Rejoicing', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of tribulation and the call to rejoice despite it. 1 Peter speaks of heaviness through temptations, while John assures peace amid tribulation, highlighting a shared theme of overcoming difficulties.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 7, 18, 23, 10, 10, 'tried with fire', 'Refining Faith and Trials', 'Both passages emphasize the process of being tested and refined through trials. 1 Peter highlights the value of faith tested by fire, while Job expresses confidence in emerging as gold after being tried.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 7, 59, 1, 12, 12, 'tried with fire', 'Endurance in Trials and Rewards', 'Both passages emphasize the value of enduring trials and temptations. 1 Peter highlights the preciousness of faith tested by fire, while James promises a crown of life for those who endure temptation.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 7, 23, 48, 10, 10, 'tried with fire', 'Refinement Through Affliction', 'Both passages emphasize the process of refinement through trials. 1 Peter speaks of faith being tested like gold, while Isaiah mentions being refined in the furnace of affliction. This connection highlights the value of enduring hardships for spiritual growth.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 7, 60, 4, 12, 12, NULL, 'Connection of Trials and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of trials, specifically referring to them as ''fiery'' and highlighting their significance in testing faith. The first passage presents trials as precious, while the second encourages believers not to be surprised by them.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 7, 59, 1, 3, 4, 'trial of your faith', 'Connection of Faith Trials', 'Both passages emphasize the ''trial of your faith'' as a process that leads to spiritual growth. 1 Peter highlights the value of faith tested by fire, while James focuses on how this trial produces patience, leading to perfection.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 7, 38, 13, 9, 9, 'tried with fire', 'Refinement Through Trials', 'Both passages emphasize the process of being refined through fire, highlighting the value of faith and the testing of believers. They illustrate how trials serve to purify and strengthen one''s relationship with God.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 7, 20, 17, 3, 3, 'tried with fire', 'Testing of Faith and Hearts', 'Both passages emphasize the process of testing and refinement. 1 Peter speaks of faith being tested like gold, while Proverbs highlights the Lord''s testing of hearts, suggesting a parallel in the value of trials.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 8, 43, 20, 29, 29, 'having not seen, ye love', 'Belief Without Sight', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of believing without seeing. 1 Peter 1:8 speaks of loving and rejoicing in Christ without having seen Him, while John 20:29 highlights the blessing of those who believe without sight. This connection highlights the significance of faith in the unseen.', 'theme', 0.6359999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 8, 47, 5, 7, 7, 'ye love; in whom, though now ye see him not', 'Faith and Belief Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of faith over physical sight. 1 Peter highlights joy in believing without seeing, while 2 Corinthians states that we walk by faith, not by sight.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 8, 45, 15, 13, 13, 'joy unspeakable and full of glory', 'Connection of Joy and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize joy and peace in believing. 1 Peter highlights rejoicing with joy unspeakable, while Romans speaks of being filled with joy and peace in believing. This connection highlights the transformative power of faith.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 8, 43, 16, 22, 22, 'rejoice with joy unspeakable', 'Connection of Joy in Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of joy arising from faith. In 1 Peter, joy is linked to believing in Christ without seeing Him, while John speaks of joy that comes from seeing Him again, suggesting a continuity of joy in the believer''s experience.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 8, 58, 11, 1, 1, 'though now ye see him not', 'Connection of Faith and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of faith in relation to the unseen. 1 Peter speaks of loving and believing in Christ whom we do not see, while Hebrews defines faith as evidence of things not seen.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 8, 47, 4, 18, 18, 'ye see him not', 'Connection of Faith and Perception', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between seen and unseen realities. 1 Peter highlights love and joy in believing without seeing, while 2 Corinthians encourages focusing on eternal, unseen things over temporal, visible ones.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 8, 60, 1, 6, 6, 'ye rejoice with joy unspeakable', 'Joy Amidst Trials', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of rejoicing despite challenges. In 1 Peter 1:6, joy is present even in heaviness, while 1 Peter 1:8 speaks of rejoicing with joy unspeakable through belief in Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 9, 45, 6, 22, 22, 'the end', 'Connection of Salvation and End', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''the end'' related to faith and life. In 1 Peter, the ''end'' refers to the salvation of souls, while in Romans, it refers to everlasting life, highlighting a shared theme of ultimate fulfillment in faith.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 9, 59, 1, 21, 21, 'salvation of your souls', 'Salvation of Souls Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of salvation for the soul. 1 Peter speaks of receiving the end of faith as salvation, while James encourages receiving the word that can save souls.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 9, 58, 11, 13, 13, 'salvation of your souls', 'Faith and Salvation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of faith leading to salvation. 1 Peter speaks of receiving the salvation of your souls, while Hebrews highlights those who died in faith, looking forward to promises not yet received.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 10, 40, 13, 17, 17, 'the prophets have enquired and searched diligently', 'Desire of Prophets and Righteous Men', 'This connection highlights the shared theme of prophets desiring to understand the salvation and grace that would come. Both passages emphasize the longing of prophets to see and hear the revelations that were fulfilled in the New Testament. The concept of prophets inquiring about future grace links the two verses.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 10, 42, 10, 24, 24, 'the prophets have enquired and searched diligently', 'Desire of Prophets and Kings', 'This connection highlights the shared theme of prophets desiring to understand the salvation and grace that would come, as noted in both passages. Both verses emphasize the longing of prophets to see and hear the revelations that were ultimately fulfilled in Christ.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
