(60, 1, 10, 27, 2, 44, 44, 'grace that should come unto you', 'Connection of Salvation and Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s promised kingdom and salvation. Both passages emphasize the enduring nature of God''s plan, with the prophets seeking understanding of the grace and kingdom that would come.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 10, 43, 5, 39, 39, 'of the grace that should come unto you', 'Connection of Salvation and Scriptures', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation as both passages emphasize the search for truth. In 1 Peter, the prophets sought the grace to come, while in John, the scriptures are said to testify of eternal life through Christ.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 10, 44, 7, 52, 52, 'prophets have enquired and searched diligently', 'Prophets and Their Messages', 'Both passages emphasize the role of prophets in foretelling the coming of salvation and the Just One. The SOURCE verse highlights the prophets'' diligent search for grace, while the TARGET passage points to their persecution for proclaiming this message.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 10, 44, 10, 43, 43, 'the prophets have enquired and searched diligently', 'Connection of Prophetic Witness', 'This connection highlights the role of the prophets in foretelling salvation. Both passages emphasize that the prophets prophesied about grace and witness to the belief in Jesus for the remission of sins.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 11, 23, 52, 13, 14, 'the sufferings of Christ', 'Connection of Suffering and Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of suffering leading to glory. Both passages refer to the sufferings of a servant, with Isaiah describing the marred visage and 1 Peter referencing the Spirit of Christ testifying to these sufferings and the subsequent glory.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 11, 61, 1, 21, 21, 'the Spirit of Christ which was in them', 'Connection of Prophecy and Inspiration', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Spirit in revealing prophecies about Christ. 1 Peter discusses the Spirit of Christ testifying about future sufferings and glory, while 2 Peter highlights that prophecies were spoken by holy men moved by the Holy Ghost.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 11, 42, 24, 25, 27, 'the sufferings of Christ, and the glory', 'Connection of Suffering and Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of Christ''s sufferings and subsequent glory. Both passages emphasize the prophetic significance of these events, with 1 Peter referencing the Spirit of Christ testifying beforehand and Luke showing Jesus explaining the necessity of these sufferings.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 11, 45, 8, 9, 9, 'the Spirit of Christ', 'Connection of the Spirit of Christ', 'This connection highlights the role of the Spirit of Christ in both passages. In 1 Peter, the Spirit signifies the sufferings and glory of Christ, while Romans emphasizes the necessity of having the Spirit of Christ to belong to Him.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 11, 23, 53, 1, 12, 'sufferings of Christ', 'Connection of Suffering and Glory', 'This connection highlights the prophetic nature of Isaiah 53, which details the sufferings of the servant, paralleling the ''sufferings of Christ'' mentioned in 1 Peter 1:11. Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering leading to eventual glory.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 11, 44, 26, 22, 23, 'the sufferings of Christ, and the glory', 'Connection of Suffering and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the suffering of Christ and the subsequent glory that follows. 1 Peter speaks of the Spirit of Christ testifying to these events, while Acts highlights the fulfillment of these prophecies through Christ''s resurrection.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 11, 1, 3, 15, 15, 'the sufferings of Christ', 'Connection of Suffering and Glory', 'This connection highlights the prophetic nature of suffering and glory found in both passages. Genesis 3:15 speaks of enmity and a future victory, while 1 Peter 1:11 refers to the sufferings of Christ and the glory that follows, linking the two themes of suffering and ultimate triumph.', 'prophecy', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 12, 43, 15, 26, 26, 'Holy Ghost sent down from heaven', 'Connection of the Holy Spirit', 'This connection highlights the role of the Holy Spirit in revealing truth. Both passages emphasize the Spirit''s function in testifying and ministering the gospel.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(60, 1, 12, 46, 2, 10, 10, NULL, 'Revelation by the Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit in revealing divine truths to believers. They highlight that these revelations are not for the angels or past prophets, but specifically for those who receive the gospel.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
